Rule Set: CalculatePayment

Fire mode: Explicit
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
SetNumberOfMonthsset Pre Qual Estimate Monthly Periods to 12 multiplied by Pre Qual Estimate Term Years
LoopBorrowersFor each (declared) borrower in Borrowers
Set PreQualEstimate.MonthlyPayment to Round(((PreQualEstimate.PresentValue + PreQualEstimate.Fees) * (PreQualEstimate.InterestRateDecimal/12) * ((1 + (PreQualEstimate.InterestRateDecimal/12)) ^ PreQualEstimate.MonthlyPeriods)) / ((1 + (PreQualEstimate.InterestRateDecimal/12)) ^ PreQualEstimate.MonthlyPeriods - 1), 2) Description: While InRule includes a built in function for payments (PMT) the kit shows the calculation here for reference.

Rule Set: CalculateAPR

Fire mode: Explicit Description: Calculating the APR is based on the Newton Raphson iteration. The calcuation iterates based on a derivative using the previously calculated x which is the potential APR. The formula used is from this source: https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/622643/how-to-calculate-apr-using-newton-raphson Note that this calculation is not certified and is not suitable for production use by a Loan Origination System. The purpose of this Rule Set is to demonstrate how a compliant calculation can be implemented.
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
Declare payment Declare payment as Decimal
Declare principle Declare principle as Decimal
Declare months Declare months as Integer
Declare fee Declare fee as Decimal
SetVariablesTake the following actions:
    set payment to Pre Qual Estimate Monthly Payment
    set principle to Pre Qual Estimate Present Value
    set fee to Pre Qual Estimate Fees
    set months to Pre Qual Estimate Monthly Periods
    fire notification "payment = <% payment %>"
    fire notification "principle = <% principle %>"
    fire notification "months = <% months %>"
    fire notification "fee = <% fee %>"
Declare previousx Declare previousx as Decimal Description: As the iterations run, the previous x will be compared to the new x so we know when to stop.
Declare f Declare f as Decimal Description: Variable for the primary calcuation (the numerator).
Declare fp Declare fp as Decimal Description: The derivative of f (the denominator).
Declare X Declare X as Decimal Description: This variable represents the potential new APR.
Set X Set X to Round((months * payment - principle) / ((((months * (months + 1)) / 2) * payment) + fee), 8)
Set previousx Set previousx to X
NotifyWithXfire notification "Initial X = <% X %>"
Declare APR Declare APR as Decimal set to 0 Description: The final APR value.
Declare flag Declare flag as Integer set to 0 Description: Used to stop the iterations.
IterationsWhile flag = 0 Do
Set f to principle * X * (1 + X) + (fee * X^2) - payment * (1 + X - (1 + X)^(1 - months))
Set fp to principle * (1 + (2 * X)) + (2 * fee * X) - (payment * (1 - ((months - 1) * (1 + X))^-months))
Set previousx to X
Set X to X - (f / fp)
Take the following actions:
    fire notification "f = " & f & " fp = " & fp & " previousx = " & previousx & " X = " & X & " Flag value = " & absolute value of X minus previousx with the following settings:
        as informational
        allow multiple notifications
If Abs(X - previousx) < 0.0000000000000001 Then
Set flag to 1
Set APR Set APR to X * 12 * 10000 / 100
FinalNotificationfire notification "The APR is estimated to be: <% APR %>"
SetFinalAPRset Pre Qual Estimate APR to APR

Rule Set: CalculateSchedule

Fire mode: Explicit Description: The calculated schedule does not cleanly end at 0. The final payment should be adjusted for any potential over-payment.
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
Declare month Declare month as Integer set to 0
Declare principle Declare principle as Decimal set to 0
Declare interestpayment Declare interestpayment as Decimal set to 0
Declare principlepayment Declare principlepayment as Decimal set to 0
Declare endingprinciple Declare endingprinciple as Decimal set to 0
StartingValuesTake the following actions:
    set month to 1
    set principle to Pre Qual Estimate Fees plus Pre Qual Estimate Present Value rounded to 2 decimal places
    set interestpayment to principle multiplied by Pre Qual Estimate Interest Rate Decimal divided by 12 rounded to 2 decimal places
    set principlepayment to Pre Qual Estimate Monthly Payment minus interestpayment rounded to 2 decimal places
    set endingprinciple to principle minus principlepayment rounded to 2 decimal places 		Description: Setup the initial values prior to the while loop. This provides the first entry into the collection.
EvaluatePeriodsWhile month < PreQualEstimate.MonthlyPeriods + 1 Do
Display Month: <% month %> Balance: <% principle %> Payment: <% PreQualEstimate.MonthlyPayment %> PreQual Interest Payment: <% interestpayment %> Principle Payment: <% principlepayment %> Ending Balance: <% endingprinciple %> Description: Output the notification of the payment.
Add member to PreQualEstimate.PaymentSchedule

Field nameValue
Balanceprinciple
PaymentPreQualEstimate.MonthlyPayment
Periodmonth
InterestPartinterestpayment
PrinciplePartprinciplepayment
EndingBalanceendingprinciple
 Description: Add the payment detail to the collection.
Take the following actions:
    set month to month plus 1
    set principle to endingprinciple rounded to 2 decimal places
    set interestpayment to principle multiplied by Pre Qual Estimate Interest Rate Decimal divided by 12 rounded to 2 decimal places
    set principlepayment to Pre Qual Estimate Monthly Payment minus interestpayment rounded to 2 decimal places
    set endingprinciple to principle minus principlepayment rounded to 2 decimal places 		Description: Set the new values for the next iteration.

Rule Set: EnforceLoanLimit

Fire mode: Explicit Description: Establish that the loan is within the defined limits based on location given by FannieMae.
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
GetPrimaryBorrowerFor each (declared) borrower in Borrowers
Take the following actions:
    set Pre Qual Estimate State to convert borrower Property Detail State to upper case
    set Pre Qual Estimate City to convert borrower Property Detail City to upper case
SetLoanLimitFromQuer... Take the following actions:
    set Pre Qual Estimate Loan Limit One Unit to GetLoanLimitOneUnit (state = Pre Qual Estimate State, city = Pre Qual Estimate City)
    set Pre Qual Estimate Loan Limit Two Unit to GetLoanLimitTwoUnit (state = Pre Qual Estimate State, city = Pre Qual Estimate City)
    set Pre Qual Estimate Loan Limit Three Unit to GetLoanLimitThreeUnit (state = Pre Qual Estimate State, city = Pre Qual Estimate City)
    set Pre Qual Estimate Loan Limit Four Unit to GetLoanLimitFourUnit (state = Pre Qual Estimate State, city = Pre Qual Estimate City)
EnforceLimitIf
     Pre Qual Estimate Present Value is greater or equal to Pre Qual Estimate Loan Limit One Unit
Then
    fire notification "This loan exceeds the limits for this specific investor for the city of <% PreQualEstimate.City %> and state <% PreQualEstimate.State %>"
    add collection member 'AddMessageForLimit'
Else
    fire notification "This loan is within the limit for this specific investor considering the city of <% PreQualEstimate.City %> and state <% PreQualEstimate.State %>"
    add collection member 'AddInformationMessageForLimit'

Rule Set: CalculateAndEnforceDTI

Fire mode: Explicit
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
EvalutateBorrowersFor each (declared) borrower in Borrowers
Take the following actions:
    set Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Income to Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Income plus borrower MonthlyIncome
    set Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Income to Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Income plus borrower OtherIncomeTotal
    set Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Debt to Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Debt plus borrower Liabilities Monthly Total
    set Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Debt to Pre Qual Estimate Total Monthly Debt plus borrower Other Liabilities Monthly Total
Set PreQualEstimate.DTI Set PreQualEstimate.DTI to PreQualEstimate.TotalMonthlyDebt/PreQualEstimate.TotalMonthlyIncome Description: Establish the overall debt to income ratio.
EnforceDTIIf
     Pre Qual Estimate DTI is greater than 0.45
Then
    fire notification "This loan exceeds the DTI limits of some investors. DTI: <% PreQualEstimate.DTI %>"
    add collection member 'AddDTIMessageExceeds'
Else
    fire notification "This loan is within acceptable DTI limits of some investors. DTI: <% PreQualEstimate.DTI %>"
    add collection member 'AddInfoDTIMessage'

Rule Set: Totals

Fire mode: Explicit
Rule or ActionDetailDescription, Notes, and Categories
LoopOtherLiabilitiesFor each (declared) otherliability in OtherLiabilities
Set Borrower.OtherLiabilitiesMonthlyTotal to Borrower.OtherLiabilitiesMonthlyTotal + otherliability.MonthlyPayment
LoopLiabilitiesFor each (declared) liability in Liabilities
Set Borrower.LiabilitiesTotal to Borrower.LiabilitiesTotal + liability.UnpaidBalance
Set Borrower.LiabilitiesMonthlyTotal to Borrower.LiabilitiesMonthlyTotal + liability.MonthlyPayment
IncludeOtherLiabilit... set Liabilities Monthly Total to Liabilities Monthly Total plus Other Liabilities Monthly Total
LoopOtherAssetsFor each (declared) otherasset in OtherAssets
Set Borrower.OtherAssetsTotal to Borrower.OtherAssetsTotal + otherasset.Value
LoopAssetsFor each (declared) asset in Assets
Set Borrower.AssetsTotal to Borrower.AssetsTotal + asset.Value
IncludeOtherAssetsset Assets Total to Assets Total plus Other Assets Total Description: Adds in other assets for a complete total.
LoopOtherIncomeFor each (declared) otherincome in OtherIncome
Set Borrower.OtherIncomeTotal to Borrower.OtherIncomeTotal + otherincome.Amount
LoopEmployersFor each (declared) employer in Employers
Set Borrower.MonthlyIncome to Borrower.MonthlyIncome + employer.Income.Total + employer.OwnerMonthlyIncome Description: Total both the income parts from the employer and any income resulting from business ownership.
IncludeOtherIncomeset this Borrower MonthlyIncome to MonthlyIncome plus OtherIncomeTotal Description: Adds other income to the monthly total.
